cultural and literary heritage. Giving readers a window into the material culture and enthusiasms of Second Empire France, it provides the first English translations of 1869’s Manual of the Velocipede, 1868’s Note on Monsieur Michaux’s Velocipede, and the 1869 operetta Dagobert and his Velocipede. It also reprints scores of rare images from newspapers and advertisements, analyzing how these magnificent machines captured the era’s visual imagination. By looking at how it influenced French attitudes towards politics, national identity, technology, fashion, fitness, and gender roles, this book shows how the short-lived craze of velocipedomania had a big impact.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCyclingzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aPopular culturezFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aVelocipedesxHistoryvSources. 0aVelocipedeszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 7aTechnology & Engineering / General.2bisacsh  avelocipede, cycling history, cycling and literature, operetta, French Second Empire, cycling and poetry, cycling manuals, Nineteenth-century France, bicycle history, sports and recreation, sports history, biking, bicycles, cycling, cheap bicycle, history of bicycles, bicycle manufacturing, French bicycle culture, bicycle culture, biking culture, prohibition, gangsternew york18th amendmentprohibition, gangster, new York, 18th amendment, gangs, mobsters, Chicago, 1920s, mob.1 aWhidden, Seth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099422308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gru